main event: A flying saucer was observed over northern Norway on March 19, 1958, and was tracked on radar as it passed over the island of Feodosy.
interesting points: The flying saucer was reported to be elliptical in shape and accompanied by a humming or whistling sound.
The Norwegian Air Force conducted preliminary and follow-up investigations, confirming the presence of an unidentified flying object.
The sighting was observed by several witnesses in the area at the time.
The conclusion of the report suggests that the observed object was probably a balloon, though it could also be possibly astronomical or of aircraft origin.
The observation was based on lights, as the surrounding area visibility was reported as insufficient for detailed evaluation.
sighted object: an unidentified flying object described as a flying saucer
